/blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you were in the process of=C2=A0<em>negotia=
ting </em>a merger, and then you got nervous that some element of the compa=
ny=E2=80=99s business might not be what you thought, you might put the nego=
tiations =E2=80=9Con hold.=E2=80=9D You might demand more information about=
 the company=E2=80=99s bot calculations, and you might stop negotiating oth=
er details of the deal until you got it. If the information wasn=E2=80=99t =
what you wanted, you might walk away, or demand a lower price. All of these=
 things are things that could happen before you sign a merger agreement. No=
t, generally, after.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday there was a big hearing in Delaware =
Chancery Court on the Musk/Twitter lawsuit. Some of it was about discovery =
issues =E2=80=94=C2=A0Musk and Twitter have been demanding information from=
 each other, and fighting about what they have to provide and when. But the=
 more important part was about whether Musk can amend his claims to add mor=
e reasons to get out of the deal. Initially, Musk argued that he could get =
out of his deal to buy Twitter mostly for reasons relating to his apparent =
belief that Twitter has too many bots. But then last month Twitter=E2=80=99=
s former head of security, Peiter =E2=80=9CMudge=E2=80=9D Zatko, publicized=
 a whistle-blower complaint arguing that Twitter does a bunch of other bad =
things, and Musk wants to add those claims to his arguments. If Twitter has=
 bad information security practices, then maybe that=E2=80=99s fraud, or ma=
ybe its representations are false and there=E2=80=99s=C2=A0a material adver=
se effect, and Musk might as well argue that too.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At the hearing, Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers argued =
that Zatko=E2=80=99s claims=C2=A0might be true, and if they are then they m=
ight give Musk a way out of the deal, and so we=C2=A0might as well find out=
. And Twitter=E2=80=99s lawyers argued that Musk is just fishing for excuse=
s to get out of the deal.=C2=A0(Disclosure, Twitter=E2=80=99s lawyers are a=
t Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen &amp; Katz, where I used to work.) As Bloomberg=
=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2897703=
