<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A brief update on Digital World Acquisition Co=
rp., the special purpose acquisition company that has signed a deal to take=
 Donald Trump=E2=80=99s social media company public. We <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28977032.259543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMDYvdHJ1bXAtc3BhYy1kb2Vzbi10=
LWhhdmUtdGhlLXZvdGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MDcyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1=
haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW=
9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfcfbf7e2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked yesterday<=
/a> about how it has to close the deal by tomorrow or else close up shop an=
d return $10.20 per share to shareholders, unless it gets an extension. It =
has asked its shareholders to vote on a one-year extension, but it needs 65=
% of them to vote yes, and I guess they are hard to reach; so far it doesn=
=E2=80=99t seem to have enough votes, and it has delayed the vote to the la=
st minute to round up some more.=C2=A0DWAC=E2=80=99s managers can also unil=
aterally give themselves=C2=A0up to two three-month extensions, but (1) it=
=E2=80=99s not clear that=E2=80=99s enough time and (2) they have to pay $2=
.875 million for each extension, from their own money, and it=E2=80=99s not=
 clear that=E2=80=99s a good gamble. I mean, if the odds are 50 to 1 agains=
t the deal closing, it=E2=80=99s a good gamble; they will get paid very wel=
l if the deal closes. But if the odds are 100 to 1 against, probably not. W=
hen we discussed this yesterday they had not said yet if they=E2=80=99d put=
 up the money, which perhaps suggests something about the odds.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Slightly belatedly, though, DWAC <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28977032.259543/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMjM4ODY1L2=
QzOTI1NDZkZGVmYTE0YS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa703c47b" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> annou=
nced yesterday</a> that they=E2=80=99ll pay up if they have to:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the Extension Amendment is not =
approved by the stockholders by September 8, 2022, ARC Global Investments I=
I, LLC, the Company=E2=80=99s sponsor (the =E2=80=9CSponsor=E2=80=9D), inte=
nds to contribute to the Company=E2=80=99s trust account an aggregate amoun=
t of $2,875,000, which is equal to $0.10 per share of Class A common stock =
issued in the Company=E2=80=99s initial public offering, to extend the time=
 to consummate an initial business combination for a three-month period, un=
til December 8, 2022.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So there you go.</p>
